<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>

<h1 style="color: blue;">This is a Blue Heading</h1>

<style>
body {background-color: powderblue;}
h1 {color: blue;}
p {color: red;}	
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph</p>

</body>
</html>



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text.css" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is heading</h1>
<p>This is paragraph</p>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
h1 {
	color: blue;
	font-family: verdana;
	font-size: 300%;

}	
p {
	color: red;
	font-family: courier;
	font-size: 160%;

}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph</p>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#p01 {
	color: blue;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<p>This is a paragraph</p>
<p>This is a paragraph</p>
<p id="p01">I am different.</p>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#p01 {
	border: 1px solid powderblue;
	padding: 30px;
}
p {
	border: 1px solid powderblue;
}
p.error {
	color: red;
} 
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>

<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<p class="error">I am different</p>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<p class="error">I am different too.</p>

<p id="p01">This is a paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
a:link {
	color: green;
	background-color: transparent;
	text-decoration: none;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>HTML Links</h1>
<p><a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/">Visit our HTML tutorial</a></p>

<h2>Local Links</h2>

<p><a href="html_images.asp">HTML Images</a> is a link to a page on this webiste.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.w3.org/">W3C</a> is a link to a website on the World Wide Web.</p>

<h3>Link Colors</h3>

<p>You can change the default colors of links</p>

<a href="html_images.asp" target="_blank">HTML Images</a>

<a href="html_images.asp" style="text-decoration: none"> HTML Images</a>

<h4>The target Attribute</h4>

<a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/" target="_blank"> Visit our HTML tutorial!</a>

<p>If you set the target attribute to "_blank", the link will open in a new browser window or tab.</p>

<h4>Image LInks</h4>

<p>The image is a link. You can click on it.</p>

<a href="default.asp">
	<img src="smiley.gif" alt="HTML tutorial"
style="width: 42px;height: 42px;border: 0">
</a>

<p>We have added "border:0" to prevent IE9 (and earlier) from displaying a border around the image.</p>

<p>Locked in a frame? <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/"
target="_top">Click here!</a></p>

</body>
</html>

